raramdisk.c : this is a block driver which assumes RAM as a block device 
  

   Testing the driver:

		1) make 
		2) insert the module (device node is created with the name sbd0)
		3) Create a file system on the device 
			# mkfs.ext3 /dev/sbd0
		4) Mount the device 
			# mount /dev/sbd0 /mnt
		5)Create files and check in /mnt
		6)umount the device (umount /dev/sbd0)
		7)Remove the module

